<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-19T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-19T13:00:00-05:00" n="266" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d266">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">810.154/257: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-19T12:00:00-06:00">October 19,
                                1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 10:52 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>102. Department’s telegram No. 61, October 11, 4 p.m. Minister of Fomento
                            states agreeable if engineers come about November 1st but not later,
                            during rainy season.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>